books.author: Nicholas Sparks
books.title: The Notebook
books.description: A classic romance novel about a young couple who fall in love in the 1940s and are separated by fate, but reunite years later to rekindle their passion.

books.author: John Green
books.title: The Fault in Our Stars
books.description: A touching story of two teenagers who meet at a cancer support group and embark on a journey of love, loss, and hope.

books.author: J.D. Salinger
books.title: The Catcher in the Rye
books.description: A novel about a rebellious teenager who runs away from his boarding school and wanders around New York City, searching for meaning and authenticity.

books.author: Harper Lee
books.title: To Kill a Mockingbird
books.description: A Pulitzer Prize-winning novel about a young girl who witnesses the racial injustice and moral courage of her father, a lawyer, in the 1930s Alabama.

books.author: Gillian Flynn
books.title: Gone Girl
books.description: A thriller novel about a married couple whose relationship turns sour when the wife disappears on their fifth anniversary, leaving behind clues that suggest she may have faked her own death.

books.author: Khaled Hosseini
books.title: The Kite Runner
books.description: A sweeping saga of friendship, betrayal, redemption, and love set against the backdrop of Afghanistan’s turbulent history.

books.author: Markus Zusak
books.title: The Book Thief
books.description: A novel narrated by Death that follows the life of a young girl who steals books and shares them with others in Nazi Germany during World War II.

books.author: Kathryn Stockett
books.title: The Help
books.description: A novel based on true events that depicts the lives of African American maids working for white families in Mississippi during the 1960s civil rights movement.
